HEADWORD: Geminate
<hw>Gem"i*nate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>geminatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>genimare</ets> to double. See
<er>Gemini</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>In pairs or twains; two
together; binate; twin; <as>as, <ex>geminate</ex> flowers</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Gray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Geminate</ent>⟦br⟧

